---
import Markdown from "@xtyle/astro/Markdown.astro";
import Card from "@xtyle/astro/Card.astro";
import Stack from "@xtyle/astro/Stack.astro";
import Cluster from "@xtyle/astro/Cluster.astro";
import Heading from "@xtyle/astro/Heading.astro";
import Text from "@xtyle/astro/Text.astro";
import Badge from "@xtyle/astro/Badge.astro";

const document = `# Derivation

An **algorithm** maps a few anchors and knobs into a full, internally consistent
token set. The algorithm is the durable asset; a theme is a materialized
invocation of one. See [the derivation model](/start) for the long version.

## What it covers

1. the anchors you pin
2. the knobs you turn
3. everything else, derived

> A theme is a print. The algorithm is the press.

Inline \`--accent\` reads the same as a fence:

\`\`\`ts
const theme = derive({ bg: "#0f1115", accent: "#5b8cff" });
\`\`\`

---

Rendered with ~~a sanitizer~~ no sanitizer at all.`;

const gfm = `| component | state | notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| tooltip | fixed | tracks its trigger through scroll |
| swatch | fixed | same promotion, same defects |
| markdown | new | this one |

- [x] escape raw HTML to text
- [x] allowlist link and image URLs
- [ ] name the version

Autolinks too: https://xtyle.dev`;

const untrusted = `This came from an LLM and is rendered **as-is**:

<script>alert("this never runs")</script>
<img src=x onerror=alert("nor this")>

[a link that looks fine](javascript:alert("refused"))
and [one that is fine](https://xtyle.dev).`;

const draft = `# Edit me

Switch to **source** with the toggle, change something, and switch back.

- the textarea is the source of truth while editing
- \`input\` fires with the markdown as you type`;

const labels = [
	"Fix **tooltip** placement",
	"Refactor `AnchorTracker` in *xtyle*",
	"~~Drop~~ keep the swatch fix",
	"Review [PR #12](https://xtyle.dev)",
	"# Heading in a label",
];
---

<Stack gap={6} class="md-demo">
	<Card>
		<Stack slot="header" gap={1}>
			<Heading level={3} size="body">A document</Heading>
			<Text tone="muted" size="sm">
				Headings ride the type scale, rules and quotes ride the border ramp, and
				fences borrow the same <code>--code-*</code> family the Code component owns.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Markdown source={document} />
	</Card>

	<Card>
		<Stack slot="header" gap={1}>
			<Heading level={3} size="body">Tables and task lists</Heading>
			<Text tone="muted" size="sm">
				GFM is on by default. A wide table scrolls inside its own box rather than
				pushing the document sideways.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Markdown source={gfm} />
	</Card>

	<Card>
		<Stack slot="header" gap={1}>
			<Heading level={3} size="body">An inline label</Heading>
			<Text tone="muted" size="sm">
				<code>inline</code> renders emphasis with no blocks and no paragraph wrapper,
				so it inherits whatever type surrounds it. Note the last one: a leading
				<code>#</code> stays literal text instead of erupting a heading into the row.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Stack gap={3}>
			<Cluster gap={2} align="center">
				{labels.map((label) => (
					<span class="md-demo__tab">
						<Markdown inline source={label} />
					</span>
				))}
			</Cluster>
			<p class="md-demo__prose">
				The same label inside running text: a task titled <Markdown
					inline
					source="Fix **tooltip** in `AnchorTracker`"
				/> inherits this sentence's size, weight, and color rather than imposing its own.
			</p>
		</Stack>
	</Card>

	<Card>
		<Stack slot="header" gap={1}>
			<Cluster gap={2} align="center" justify="between">
				<Heading level={3} size="body">Untrusted input</Heading>
				<Badge variant="soft" tone="success">no sanitizer</Badge>
			</Cluster>
			<Text tone="muted" size="sm">
				Raw HTML is escaped to text and refused URLs lose their <code>href</code> —
				so nothing here is live. The markup below is inert text, and the first link
				is a real <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> with no destination.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Markdown source={untrusted} />
	</Card>

	<Card>
		<Stack slot="header" gap={1}>
			<Heading level={3} size="body">An editable source view</Heading>
			<Text tone="muted" size="sm">
				<code>editable</code> adds a toggle between the render and its markdown.
				The switch is a real node in the fragment fill, so a mod can reword it,
				make it an icon, or move it.
			</Text>
		</Stack>
		<Markdown editable source={draft} />
	</Card>
</Stack>

<style>
	.md-demo__prose {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: var(--text-sm);
		color: var(--fg-2);
		line-height: var(--leading-normal);
	}
	.md-demo__tab {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		padding: var(--space-1, 0.25rem) var(--space-3, 0.75rem);
		border: var(--border-thin, 1px) solid var(--field-border);
		border-radius: var(--radius-full, 999px);
		background: var(--bg-2);
		font-size: var(--text-sm);
		color: var(--fg-1);
	}
</style>
